snippet: The Australian prime minister said on Thursday that satellite imagery had detected objects in the southern Indian Ocean that might be connected to the missing Malaysia Airlines jet.
abstract: Australian Prime Min Tony Abbott says satellite imagery has detected objects that might be connected to missing Malaysia Airlines Flight 370; says an Australian Air Force Orion plane has been dispatched to the area in Indian Ocean; adds that he has informed Malaysia’s Prime Min Najib Razak of developments.

byline.original: By MICHELLE INNIS and CHRIS BUCKLEY
byline.contributor: Michelle Innis reported from Sydney, Australia, and Chris Buckley from Sepang, Malyasia. Reporting was contributed by Kirk Semple from Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia; Michael S. Schmidt and Eric Schmitt from Washington; and Mike McIntire from New York.

lead_paragraph: The Australian prime minister said on Thursday that satellite imagery had detected objects in the southern Indian Ocean that might be connected to the missing Malaysia Airlines jet.

headline.main: Newly Detected Objects Draw Searchers for Malaysian Plane
headline.print_headline: Newly Detected Objects Draw Plane’s Searchers
